snippet.textDisplay: Ryland keep being cheerful and making people smile.  I’m a bit down this holiday season as my moms heart valve she had replaced last year is failing.  Her heart muscle itself is dying.  Now they are talking about her needing a heart pump.  I know it’ll help her but it’s a lot to take in.   I have my own health issues, money doesn’t grow on trees to fix repairs needed and life in general.  Holiday stuff isn’t even up.  I feel so rushed this year. 😢. Shane—— I understand.  I’m not super happy with myself either. But people gonna do what they do. You can’t live life worried about what people will think.  Just do what you want to.  Your very blessed.  Please focus on the happy things. So many people out there have less and just keep trucking along.  No disrespect given to either of you.  Let’s make a pact.  If I can try to smile even though it may be my last Christmas with my Mom and I have nothing really to give but my love and time then you guys can too.  Many hugs.  Ryland you are a gem.  A positive friendly gem.  I wish I knew you in real life.  Shane smile ❤️. Merry Christmas to you and yours.
